---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="shivzee // why esp?"
  description="Why I host my personal site on an ESP32 microcontroller."
  currentPath="/why"
>
  <section class="px-6 md:px-14 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-14 border-b border-[#161616]">
    <div class="text-[#383838] text-xl tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-4">
      [ entry_002 ]
    </div>
    <h1
      class="text-6xl md:text-8xl text-[#c8ff00] leading-none tracking-tight mb-6"
    >
      Why?
    </h1>
    <h2
      class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-[#d0d0d0] font-light tracking-tight leading-snug max-w-3xl mt-8"
    >
      I'm an engineer dude, <br /><span class="text-[#c8ff00] italic"
        >what do you expect?</span
      >
    </h2>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 md:px-14 py-16">
    <div class="text-[#383838] text-lg tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-10">
      [ the_real_reason ]
    </div>

    <div
      class="max-w-2xl space-y-8 text-xl text-[#777] tracking-wide leading-relaxed"
    >
      <p>
        Jokes apart, the real story is much simpler. <strong
          class="text-[#c8ff00] font-normal">I was just really bored.</strong
        >
      </p>

      <p>
        I was sitting at my desk, staring at this tiny ESP32 microcontroller
        catching dust in the corner. I already run a full-blown homelab to
        self-host my stuff, so I figured, why not make this little guy carry
        some of the weight?
      </p>

      <p>
        Around the same time, I had been reading up on <strong
          class="text-[#c8ff00] font-normal">Cloudflare Durable Objects</strong
        > and stateful edge computing. The tech seemed like absolute black magic,
        and I desperately wanted an excuse to play with it. It just clicked what if
        I tied them together?
      </p>

      <p>
        Honestly? There is zero practical reason to host a website on hardware
        that most people use to blink LEDs or read temperature sensors. But as
        engineers, we don't always build things because they're sensible. We
        build them <strong class="text-[#c8ff00] font-normal"
          >just for fun</strong
        >.
      </p>

      <p>
        I wanted to see what happens when you push the absolute limits of a $4
        chip. I wanted to prove to myself that <strong
          class="text-[#c8ff00] font-normal">engineering has no limits</strong
        > unless you accept them. And let's be real the look on people's faces when
        I tell them my personal site runs on an ESP32 is worth every single segmentation
        fault.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-20 pt-10 border-t border-[#161616] max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-2xl text-[#444] tracking-wide leading-relaxed max-w-lg">
        You're reading this served from a hardware that most people use to blink
        LEDs.
        <span class="text-[#c8ff00]"> That's the whole point.</span>
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-8">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="text-[#444] hover:text-[#c8ff00] text-xl tracking-widest transition-colors"
        >
          ← back_home
        </a>
        <a
          href="/how"
          class="text-[#444] hover:text-[#c8ff00] text-xl tracking-widest transition-colors"
        >
          ~/how →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
